# Sprint 2 cycle-5 fixture (paper §4.3 attention sinks API surface v0).
#
# Pins the "sinks disabled" sentinel path: when `@attention_sink` is
# OMITTED, the decorator-extraction site leaves `num_sink_tokens=0` (the
# local-default) and compilation flows through cleanly with no refusal.
#
# This is the ONLY way users can express "sinks off" — the semantic
# checker rejects `@attention_sink(tokens=0)` up front (Rule 3a in
# `nsl-semantic/tests/attention_sink_decorator.rs`), so omission is the
# sentinel.
#
# Companion to `attention_sink_decorator.nsl`, which carries
# `tokens=4` and (post-Sprint-2-cycle-5) hits the codegen refusal.

@flash_attention
fn forward():
    pass
